# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?

Chatbot Professor Rosen

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")

Drawing inspiration from this project https://data-flair.training/blogs/python-chatbot-project/ in which they created a chatbot that had healthcare applicatoins, I would use a similar method to create a chatbot that could be used to teach python instead. 


## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?
I would like to make a generative based chatbot,  but I think in this case a retrieval based chatbot makes the most sense, and essentially I would take all the major topics  that we learned this semester and make a chatbot that would be able to teach them to a student that wants to learn them. 
Bascially a chatbot Professor Rosen. The goal is that the ChatBot is able to:

1. Explain major concepts discussed in course i.e for loops, if statements, Regular expressions, IDE's explain basics on how to use IDLE, pycharm and Visual Studio, file reading, etc
2. Provide examples of working code for each of the major topics
3. Be able to answer some common questions
For the execution I plan to use the source code from the project I drew inspiration from to make the basic UI, then for the information in the chatbot I would use the material learned from class. Ideally, the hope is that someone would get the same information out of this chatbot that I obtained from attending a college level course, and be able to learn it at their own pace.
